title: Gazelle 85 Shoes
description: Born in the '60s, the adidas Gazelle sneakers have a long and rich history on the pitch. For this pair, we're giving some love to a lesser-known version released in 1985. It still has the low-key look and 3-Stripes you're familiar with, but all the other details have been refined. The suede is smooth, the tooling is taller and the pattern is reworked with just the right amount of fresh. No longer made for training, these shoes are pure adidas style.

title: Gazelle Shoes Kids
description: Comfortable juniors' shoes with signature style in soft suede. This retro revival for juniors of a '90s icon lets you step into original street style. First released in 1971, the adidas Gazelle shoes paved the way for modern casual wear and sporting culture.

title: Seattle Sounders Gazelle Shoes
description: The Seattle Sounders Gazelle Shoes by Adidas are a special edition that celebrates the team's 50th anniversary. They incorporate elements from the team's visual identity, including the Orca Mark on the tongue of the shoe, the adidas trefoil mark on the heel in Pacific Blue, and Rave Green stripes along the sides. These shoes have a white base color, which contrasts nicely with the team colors, making them stylish and comfortable for fans. They are available for purchase at Pro Shop locations and online

title: Y-3 Gazelle
description: Loved for decades, the adidas Gazelle shoes stay classic. Here they're reimagined through the viewpoint of Y-3, bringing a rich, uniform look to the soft suede that extends from the upper all the way to the tooling. The inside is lined with leather and suede, and Yohji Yamamoto's signature delivers the final signoff.
